}} '8' ('eight' ) is the natural number following 7 and preceding 9. The SI
prefix for 1000 8 is yotta (Y), and for its reciprocal, yocto (y). It
is the root word of two other numbers: [[18 (number)|eighteen]] (eight and ten)
and [[80 (number)|eighty]] (eight tens). Linguistically, it is derived from
Middle English eighte, and is presumably related to the French huit.
